description:
A Wounded Bird

Aired on 01/30/2005, Narrated by Jonathan Aris

On 21 August 1995, Atlantic Southeast Airlines Flight 529, an Embraer EMB 120 Brasilia, is climbing to its cruising altitude when a blade on the left-side propeller comes off. The imbalance of the rotating propeller causes the engine to partly tear itself from its mounting, creating excessive drag. The aircraft rapidly loses altitude and crashes, killing nine people. Metal fatigue in the propeller blade caused its failure.
